uco-core:hasFacet.rdfs:comment: NOTE: Though the user-interface actions taken to create the partition system and each of its child partitions are each potentially time-stampable, separate uco-action:Actions, the Facet design pattern means the generating InvestigativeAction cannot be broken out into separate Actions.  The partition list must be generated and populated at the time of the creation of this Partition System object.  Hence, the act of creating the child partitions is instead represented as part of the multi-minute single Action that creates and populates the partition system.

@graph.rdfs:comment: This event was the generation of the extended partition table and its contained partition.

The precise timestamp of this file deletion event was not recorded, but it is known to have occurred.  This event invalidates (ends) a Relationship FIRST.TXT had with its file system, leaving FIRST.TXT in a marked-unallocated state apparent from a superseding Relationship.

This File object avoids using the uco-observable:fileName property because that property changes values in this scenario, suggesting the need for a Quality to represent how this file's name is represented.
